16 府 Government

  • Go to
  • Meaning
  • Reading
  • Similar Kanji
  • Found In Vocabulary
  • Progress

Radical Combination

  • 广 Canopy
  • 付 Attach

Meaning

Primary

Government

Mnemonic

A canopy attaching your entire country is the government. They loom over you all and try to keep you all organized and together under their control.

Hints

Picture a map of the world with actual canopies attached to each government, representing the ruling governments of each place.

Note

Readings

On’yomi

ふ

Kun’yomi

None

Nanori

None

Mnemonic

Try to get out from under this government canopy and you'll be labeled a fool (ふ). Unless... you can fool them!

Hints

Think of all the people who've been labeled as fools by the government because they try to detach themselves from under their reach. It's a pretty long list...
